       home.sessionVariables
           Environment variables to always set at login.

           The values may refer to other environment variables using POSIX.2
           style variable references. For example, a variable parameter may be
           referenced as ‘$parameter’ or ‘${parameter}’. A default value ‘foo’
           may be given as per ‘${parameter:-foo}’ and, similarly, an
           alternate value ‘bar’ can be given as per ‘${parameter:+bar}’.

           Note, these variables may be set in any order so no session
           variable may have a runtime dependency on another session variable.
           In particular code like

               home.sessionVariables = {
                 FOO = "Hello";
                 BAR = "$FOO World!";
               };

           may not work as expected. If you need to reference another session
           variable, then do so inside Nix instead. The above example then
           becomes

               home.sessionVariables = {
                 FOO = "Hello";
                 BAR = "${config.home.sessionVariables.FOO} World!";
               };

