       services.xcape.mapExpression
           The value has the grammar ‘Key[|OtherKey]’.

           The list of key names is found in the header file X11/keysymdef.h
           (remove the ‘XK_’ prefix). Note that due to limitations of X11
           shifted keys must be specified as a shift key followed by the key
           to be pressed rather than the actual name of the character. For
           example to generate “{” the expression ‘Shift_L|bracketleft’ could
           be used (assuming that you have a key with “{” above “[”).

           You can also specify keys in decimal (prefix #), octal (#0), or
           hexadecimal (#0x). They will be interpreted as keycodes unless no
           corresponding key name is found.

           Type: attribute set of string

           Default: { }

