       systemd.user.startServices
           Whether new or changed services that are wanted by active targets
           should be started. Additionally, stop obsolete services from the
           previous generation.

           The alternatives are

               ‘suggest’ (or ‘false’)
                   Use a very simple shell script to print suggested systemctl
                   commands to run. You will have to manually run those
                   commands after the switch.

               ‘legacy’ (or ‘true’)
                   Use a Ruby script to, in a more robust fashion, determine
                   the necessary changes and automatically run the systemctl
                   commands.

               ‘sd-switch’
                   Use sd-switch, a third party application, to perform the
                   service updates. This tool offers more features while
                   having a small closure size. Note, it requires a fully
                   functional user D-Bus session. Once tested and deemed
                   sufficiently robust, this will become the default.

           Type: boolean or one of “suggest”, “legacy”, “sd-switch”

           Default: "suggest"

